          ],
          "FACILITY": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "facility": [
                  "VDG"
                ],
                "institute": "2SF HLS"
              },
              "free_text": [
                "2.5MV Van de Graaff accelerator"
              ]
            }
          ],
          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "For absolute resonance stregth measurements:",
                "The Ne tagets were prepared by implanting 20Ne+,21Ne+,",
                "22Ne+ ions at several energies in the range 5-50 keV",
                "into 1.0 mm thick carbon backings in the isotope",
                "separator. The collected amounts of the 20Ne,21Ne,22Ne",
                "nuclei were about 7 micro-g/cm2. The thicknesses of the",
                "Ne targets were about 10 keV for 1.2 MeV protons. The",
                "ration of the Ne atom number to the C atom number in",
                "the Ne targers was about 0.1.",
                "For relative resonance stregth measurements:",
                "The Ne tagets were prepared by implanting 21Ne ions",
                "into Ta backings at the collection energies of 8 and 40",
                "keV."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "GSPEC"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                ""
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "GELI"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " The germanium-lithium detector is  used with an",
                "active volume of 110 cm**3 and a resolution of 3.2 keV",
                "at Eg=2.6 MeV. The gamma-rays were detected  at an",
                "angle of 55 degrees relative to the beam.",
                "The detector was calibrated with the calibrated IAEA",
                "standard sources and using gamma-rays  from reaction",
                "27Al(p,gamma)28Si."
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "SIBAR"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                "An annular silicon surface barrier detector with",
                "an active area of 50 mm2 was used for the Ne-C ratios",
                "of the targets using backscattering of alpha-particles.",
                "It was located at a distance of 8 cm from the target",
                "giving a mean scattering angle of 178 degrees. Its",
                "resolution was 14 keV at Ealpha=2.0 MeV."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "ANALYSIS": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "In REACTIONs in the formula of resonance strength:",
                "          g*Gamma(i)Gamma(j)/Gamma(tot)",
                "instead of usual statistical weight:",
                "  g=(2J+1)/(2Jp+1)(2Jt+1), the authors used g=(2J+1)",
                "where is Jp = spin of incident projectile and",
                "Jt = spin of target nucleus."
              ]
            }
          ],
